SIMPLE: subsoil
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subsoil
<hw>Sub"soil`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The bed, or stratum,
of earth which lies immediately beneath the surface soil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Subsoil plow</b></col>, <cd>a plow having a share and
standard but no moldboard. It follows in the furrow made by an ordinary
plow, and loosens the soil to an additional depth without bringing it to
the surface.</cd> <au>Knight.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subsoil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subsoil
<hw>Sub"soil`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To turn up the subsoil
of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subsolary</ent>⟦br⟧
